        "timestamp": "2019-02-04 15:02:47.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThis change doesn't look like it will do what you want.\n\nProperties that are set via the SpringApplicationBuilder.properties() method are default properties, which means they will be overridden by any similar properties declared in application.properties.\n\nSince you have not removed the server.ssl.client-auth property from your application.properties, that will always take precedence. Therefore the code you have added to the Application.java will have no effect.",
        "patchset_number": 1
